                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360404-name-596" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-596" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-596" type="surname" value="EDWARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-596" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN EDWARDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Hornsby-street, Pearson-street, Kingsland. The prisoner worked for me—on the 3d of March I saw him in the kitchen—I asked him what he was going to do—he said he wanted some hay for the horses—he went into the stable, and came in again—I asked him what he had under his clothes—he said, "Nothing but old brass"—I said, "Let us look"—he ran out, and said, "Come out, and I will show you"—he ran into the stable, went out the other way, and ran off—I sent after him, and he was stopped—these two candlesticks are mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I found the candlesticks in the kitchen.</p>
